      \DiagramSquare {
        nw = {\mathsf {id} f},
        ne = {f},
        sw = {\mathsf {id} f'},
        se = {f'},
        north = {\ell _{f}},
        south = {\ell _{f'}},
        east = {\alpha },
        west = {\mathsf {id}_{\mathsf {id}} * \alpha },
      }
      \qquad 
      \DiagramSquare {
        nw = {f\mathsf {id}},
        ne = {f},
        sw = {f'\mathsf {id}},
        se = {f'},
        north = {r_{f}},
        south = {r_{f'}},
        east = {\alpha },
        west = {\alpha  * \mathsf {id}_{\mathsf {id}}},
      }

Law of middle unity: For any pair of composable 1-cells f and g, the following diagram commutes.





