where \varepsilon  is the counit defined on the right. Then naturality is a consequence of uniqueness.

Let g \in  {{\mathcal {C}}_{/{B}}} be an object. We take \varepsilon _{g}\colon \Sigma _{f}(f^{*}(g))\to g to be the following morphism.





